{"page":1,"prev_page_endpoint":null,"next_page_endpoint":null,"total_pages":1,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2014-01-28T03:05:02Z","content":"I too am being released with PTSD as a result of my tour in Afghanistan and I also have less than 10 years pensionable time. I have a wife and a small daughter that I feel like I am failing because of this. My employers are abandoning me.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shayne Baldwin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/77713523"},{"created_at":"2013-12-06T03:52:39Z","content":"I am a veteran and I see how my fellow comrades are being treated....they are being ignored and not receiving treatment for PTSD.  The Government needs to stand up and honor the promises made.  These Vets need help.....make the services they need EASY to access.  Revamp Veterans Affairs and get some people in place who have served and know what is required. It sickens me that our country is letting them down.  They risked their lives!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marlene Miller","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/38746992"},{"created_at":"2013-12-04T20:21:11Z","content":"My younger brother served","like_count":0,"author_name":"Darren  Budgell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16629037"},{"created_at":"2013-12-05T12:25:37Z","content":"Because all soldiers deserve the medical and psychological help necessary to carry on through life after serving in an arena of hostility.  As Canadians,  we are all affected by the ongoing lack of proper attention to these soldiers.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sherry Jones","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/72155021"},{"created_at":"2013-12-05T03:19:57Z","content":"Canada's service men and women deserve better!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Andrea Pretli","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/14616241"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T16:19:53Z","content":"I SIGN BECAUSE, THIS JUST CAUSE AND USEFUL !!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"ZILKA DAMIEN","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46367826"},{"created_at":"201